						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1432, Pramōdūta, Māgha, ba. 2, Guruvāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1511 January 11 Thursday.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Hanumappa,</hi> a servant of king <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇadēvarāya,</hi> set up Pēṭeya-Basava, and mentions <hi rend="bold">Hattiya-Beḷugallu</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Jakke-Nāyaka.</hi> </p>						

